        "Definition": {
          "text": "Defined as\ntemperature\n≥38°C (100.4°F).\nPeripheral temperature is not clinically accurate and central measurements are the preferred means of determining fever.\nRectal or oral\nRectal temperatures should not be performed in neutropenic patients\n[1]",
          "tables": []
        }
